We are going to create database from lambda

1. create private database

2. create lambda function and choose python 3.14.

3. Add code and add environment variable inside configuration.

4. Add pymysql layer --> create new layer -->  you can upload local laptop or you can upload from s3

5. For s3 process --> create ec2 and install git and clone this repo. 

6. go to repo --> aws s3 mv pymysql_layer.zip s3://bucker_name

7. Add the layer --> custom layer --> choose layer and version and add it.

8. Go to configuration and choose rds database --> connect to RDS database.

9. Run the lambda and check database created or not.
